1
00:01:04,427 --> 00:01:08,420
Inside a snowflake,
like the one on your sleeve...

2
00:01:11,396 --> 00:01:15,692
...there happened a story
you must see to believe.

3
00:01:31,958 --> 00:01:35,962
Way up in the mountains,
in the high range of Pontoos...

4
00:01:36,045 --> 00:01:38,840
...lay the small town of Whoville:

5
00:01:39,299 --> 00:01:40,717
The home of the Whos.

6
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:48,391
Ask any Who, and they'll have this to say:

7
00:01:48,474 --> 00:01:52,854
''There is no place like Whoville
around Christmas Day.''

8
00:01:53,354 --> 00:01:56,190
Every window was flocked,
every lamppost was dressed...

9
00:01:56,357 --> 00:02:00,653
...and the Whoville band marched
in their Christmasy best.

10
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:08,620
Merry Christmas! Merry Christmas!

11
00:02:21,591 --> 00:02:24,469
Arbor Day was fine,
and Easter was pleasant...

12
00:02:24,552 --> 00:02:27,805
...and every Saint Fizzin's day,
they ate a Fizz pheasant.

13
00:02:27,972 --> 00:02:31,976
But every Who knew,
from their twelve toes to their snout...

14
00:02:32,060 --> 00:02:36,439
...they loved Christmas the most,
without a single Who doubt.

15
00:02:41,027 --> 00:02:43,154
-Farfingle's welcomes you!
-Thank you.

16
00:02:43,529 --> 00:02:46,783
Merry Christmas!
Thank you for shopping Farfingle's!

17
00:02:47,617 --> 00:02:49,911
We got a snoozlephone
for your brother Drew...

18
00:02:49,994 --> 00:02:54,874
...and a snoozlephone for your brother Stu,
a muncle for your uncle...

19
00:02:54,999 --> 00:02:58,836
...a fant for your aunt
and a fandpa for your cousin Leon.

20
00:02:59,045 --> 00:03:01,172
So, we just need.... Cindy?

21
00:03:01,297 --> 00:03:02,799
Sale on Aisle 3!

22
00:03:02,882 --> 00:03:04,759
-Cindy Lou!
-Merry Christmas.

23
00:03:04,842 --> 00:03:07,470
Hello, Myrna. Merry Christmas, Fred.
Excuse me.

24
00:03:07,554 --> 00:03:09,097
Cindy Lou? Honey?

25
00:03:10,265 --> 00:03:11,349
-Dad?
-Yeah?

26
00:03:11,432 --> 00:03:13,393
Doesn't this seem like a bit much?

27
00:03:14,102 --> 00:03:15,895
This is what Christmas is all about!

28
00:03:16,229 --> 00:03:17,772
Can't you feel it?

29
00:03:17,855 --> 00:03:19,023
Merry Christmas!

30
00:03:19,107 --> 00:03:21,401
Thank you for shopping Farfingle's.
Wait a second!

31
00:03:21,651 --> 00:03:22,735
Your change!

32
00:03:23,027 --> 00:03:24,821
Another minute closer to Christmas!

33
00:03:27,115 --> 00:03:30,869
And, for the next five minutes only,
99 percent off!

34
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:48,720
Yes, every Who down in Whoville
liked Christmas a lot...

35
00:03:49,053 --> 00:03:52,807
...but the Grinch,
who lived just north of Whoville...

36
00:03:53,766 --> 00:03:55,143
...did not.

37
00:03:57,896 --> 00:04:00,690
Get on it, girls.
All the good mistletoe's at the top.

38
00:04:00,815 --> 00:04:04,152
-Hey, Drew, I'll race you!
-Not if I race you first.

39
00:04:04,485 --> 00:04:07,572
Last one to the top is a stinky old Grinch!

40
00:04:09,908 --> 00:04:13,328
You guys, where are we?
l think we should go back.

41
00:04:13,411 --> 00:04:15,872
What? You're scared of the Grinch!

42
00:04:16,497 --> 00:04:17,665
No!

43
00:04:18,249 --> 00:04:20,543
They say he lives up here in a big cave.

44
00:04:20,668 --> 00:04:23,379
And only comes down
when he's hungry for the taste of...

45
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:25,590
-...Who flesh!
-Drew!

46
00:04:26,466 --> 00:04:30,220
You're scared of the Grinch!
You're scared of the Grinch!

47
00:04:31,888 --> 00:04:33,514
-Are too!
-Am not!

48
00:04:36,935 --> 00:04:38,311
Wait for me!

49
00:04:48,988 --> 00:04:51,783
Go on, touch it. Touch the door.

50
00:04:51,866 --> 00:04:53,576
Do it for me, Stu.

51
00:05:25,984 --> 00:05:27,694
Well done, Max!

52
00:05:28,361 --> 00:05:31,364
Serves them right, those Yuletide-loving...

53
00:05:31,489 --> 00:05:34,826
...sickly-sweet,
nog-sucking cheer mongers!

54
00:05:36,327 --> 00:05:38,454
l really don't like them.

55
00:05:39,998 --> 00:05:41,499
No, l don't.

56
00:05:44,168 --> 00:05:45,253
Max!

57
00:05:47,297 --> 00:05:49,424
Get my cloak!

58
00:05:50,425 --> 00:05:53,595
l've been much too tolerant
of these Whovenile delinquents...

59
00:05:53,803 --> 00:05:56,723
...and their innocent, victimless pranks.

60
00:05:57,599 --> 00:06:00,518
So, they want to get to know me, do they?

61
00:06:01,019 --> 00:06:04,439
They want to spend a little quality time
with the Grinch.

62
00:06:05,982 --> 00:06:08,276
l guess l could use a little...

63
00:06:08,401 --> 00:06:10,111
...social interaction.

64
00:06:19,954 --> 00:06:21,122
Merry Christmas!

65
00:06:21,206 --> 00:06:22,832
Yeah, you bet.

66
00:06:22,916 --> 00:06:24,709
Ho, ho, ho, and stuff.

67
00:06:27,879 --> 00:06:28,880
Oh, my.

68
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:31,799
Someone has vandalized that vehicle.

69
00:06:31,966 --> 00:06:34,761
You see, Max?
The city is a dangerous place.

70
00:06:34,886 --> 00:06:37,722
The Grinch hated Christmas.
The whole Christmas season.

71
00:06:37,805 --> 00:06:38,973
Top of the day. Flatfoot.

72
00:06:39,057 --> 00:06:42,560
Now, please, don't ask why.
No one quite knows the reason.

73
00:06:42,644 --> 00:06:44,020
Here's a present for you.

74
00:06:44,103 --> 00:06:47,357
Be sure to run real fast with it.
Come on. Double time. Move.

75
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:50,401
It could be that his head
wasn’t screwed on just right.

76
00:06:50,485 --> 00:06:53,905
Or it could be, perhaps,
that his shoes were too tight.

77
00:06:53,988 --> 00:06:56,658
But I think that
the most likely reason of all...

78
00:06:56,824 --> 00:07:00,745
...may have been that his heart
was two sizes too small.

79
00:07:01,412 --> 00:07:04,582
Stranger, won't let you go
till you buy a chapeau!

80
00:07:16,511 --> 00:07:18,638
Boy, nothing beats Christmas, right?

81
00:07:19,556 --> 00:07:20,557
l guess.

82
00:07:21,432 --> 00:07:22,934
You guess?

83
00:07:23,101 --> 00:07:28,231
lt's just, l look around at you and Mom
and everyone getting all kerbobbled.

84
00:07:28,314 --> 00:07:31,109
Doesn't this seem superfluous?

85
00:07:31,234 --> 00:07:32,235
Dad!

86
00:07:32,902 --> 00:07:34,529
Dad!

87
00:07:37,115 --> 00:07:39,909
-What happened to you?
-lt was the Grinch!

88
00:07:45,623 --> 00:07:47,834
-Grinch?
-What do you want? l mean....

89
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:49,586
''Grinch? Oh, no!''

90
00:07:51,337 --> 00:07:53,798
Did someone just say, ''Grinch''?

91
00:07:54,883 --> 00:07:56,593
Hello, Mayor May-Who, sir.

92
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:00,847
Lou.

93
00:08:05,143 --> 00:08:07,520
l don't need to remind you
that this Christmas...

94
00:08:07,604 --> 00:08:10,773
...marks the one thousandth Whobilation.

95
00:08:10,857 --> 00:08:13,067
Whoville's most important celebration!

96
00:08:13,192 --> 00:08:16,946
And The Book of Who says, very clearly:

97
00:08:18,406 --> 00:08:20,700
''Every size of Who we can measure...

98
00:08:20,825 --> 00:08:24,746
''...knows that Whobilation
is a time we must treasure.''

99
00:08:24,871 --> 00:08:27,790
Now, Lou, please tell me that your boys...

100
00:08:28,291 --> 00:08:30,168
...were not up on Mount Crumpit...

101
00:08:30,293 --> 00:08:34,130
...provoking the one creature
within a billion bilometers of here...

102
00:08:34,255 --> 00:08:35,506
...who hates Christmas!

103
00:08:35,757 --> 00:08:37,467
But it was the Grinch!

104
00:08:38,343 --> 00:08:41,596
No, sir, the boys didn't see any Grinch.

105
00:08:41,888 --> 00:08:43,848
lt was, and he came after--

106
00:08:43,973 --> 00:08:46,100
l think they were up on the mountain...

107
00:08:46,184 --> 00:08:49,437
...playing with matches,
or defacing public property, or....

108
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:52,232
That's a relief.

109
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:54,400
All right, you heard the man:

110
00:08:54,525 --> 00:08:57,528
There is no Grinch problem here.

111
00:09:05,411 --> 00:09:08,998
-l need it there by tomorrow.
-Heck of a rush.

112
00:09:09,082 --> 00:09:11,626
Merry Christmas, Mo. Heck of a rush.

113
00:09:14,504 --> 00:09:15,672
But, Dad...

114
00:09:15,838 --> 00:09:17,632
...l just don't understand something.

115
00:09:18,049 --> 00:09:20,510
Why won't anyone talk about the Grinch?

116
00:09:21,261 --> 00:09:23,137
You kids and the Grinch!

117
00:09:23,763 --> 00:09:27,934
You see, Cindy,
the Grinch is a Who, who always....

118
00:09:28,101 --> 00:09:31,271
Actually, not a Who. He's more of a....

119
00:09:31,729 --> 00:09:35,066
-A what?
-Exactly, honey.

120
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:38,194
And he's a What
who doesn't like Christmas.

121
00:09:39,153 --> 00:09:41,030
Take a look at his mailbox, sweetie.

122
00:09:41,155 --> 00:09:43,950
Not a single Christmas card, in or out.

123
00:09:44,367 --> 00:09:45,618
Ever!

124
00:09:45,702 --> 00:09:46,786
But why?

125
00:09:46,953 --> 00:09:48,413
Lou, where's my mail?

126
00:09:48,621 --> 00:09:50,832
Lou! Got the wrong mail here.

127
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:53,167
Lou! l got the wrong mail!

128
00:09:55,044 --> 00:09:58,047
-l'll be right there.
-Lou, we got a problem!

129
00:09:58,256 --> 00:10:00,800
All right, we'll straighten this out.

130
00:10:04,178 --> 00:10:06,890
lt'll take them years to sort this out.

131
00:10:07,223 --> 00:10:11,311
This is his and now it's yours,
and this hers and now it's his!

132
00:10:13,146 --> 00:10:14,731
And for the rest of you:

133
00:10:16,774 --> 00:10:18,735
Jury duty! Jury duty! Jury duty!

134
00:10:18,943 --> 00:10:21,654
Blackmail. Pink slip.
Chain letter. Eviction notice.

135
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:23,907
Jury duty!

136
00:10:28,453 --> 00:10:32,624
Would you mind helping me
take this to the back room, honey?

137
00:10:33,583 --> 00:10:36,127
-Be careful of the sorting machine, right?
-Yeah.

138
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:14,374
Gesundheit.

139
00:11:23,258 --> 00:11:24,592
You're the....

140
00:11:25,093 --> 00:11:26,553
The....

141
00:11:26,803 --> 00:11:27,887
The Grinch!

142
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:33,434
That worked out nicely.

143
00:11:34,018 --> 00:11:35,353
Help!

144
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:45,613
Help me! Somebody!

145
00:11:45,905 --> 00:11:47,365
Max, let's go.

146
00:11:48,032 --> 00:11:49,993
Our work here is finished.

147
00:11:50,285 --> 00:11:51,369
Help me!

148
00:11:52,537 --> 00:11:54,122
Please help!

149
00:11:54,289 --> 00:11:56,416
That is not a chew toy!

150
00:11:56,958 --> 00:11:58,042
Stop it, Max!

151
00:11:58,334 --> 00:12:01,337
Get that out of your mouth!
You have no idea where it's been!

152
00:12:06,301 --> 00:12:07,385
Help!

153
00:12:10,013 --> 00:12:13,850
Bleeding hearts of the world, unite!

154
00:12:21,316 --> 00:12:24,027
There! Give me that!

155
00:12:24,193 --> 00:12:27,447
Don't you know you shouldn't
take things that don't belong to you?

156
00:12:27,530 --> 00:12:29,490
What's your problem?
Are you a wild animal?

157
00:12:32,327 --> 00:12:33,578
Let's go.

158
00:12:33,953 --> 00:12:35,997
Thanks for saving me.

159
00:12:42,212 --> 00:12:43,922
Saving you?

160
00:12:44,964 --> 00:12:47,008
ls that what you think l was doing?

161
00:12:50,178 --> 00:12:51,554
Wrong-o.

162
00:12:54,098 --> 00:12:58,019
l merely noticed that you were
improperly packaged, my dear.

163
00:13:00,730 --> 00:13:02,065
Hold still!

164
00:13:02,232 --> 00:13:04,025
Max, pick out a bow.

165
00:13:05,068 --> 00:13:06,778
Can l use your finger for a second?

166
00:13:07,779 --> 00:13:09,280
Hello! Hello!

167
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:15,620
-Cindy?
-Dad!

168
00:13:17,372 --> 00:13:18,623
Daddy!

169
00:13:19,165 --> 00:13:20,416
Daddy!

170
00:13:21,084 --> 00:13:22,418
What the hey...?

171
00:13:23,628 --> 00:13:24,712
Honey.

172
00:13:25,672 --> 00:13:26,923
Cindy?

173
00:13:27,215 --> 00:13:28,675
Dad! lt was amazing!

174
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:32,053
You've been practicing
your Christmas wrapping!

175
00:13:32,303 --> 00:13:33,763
l am so proud of you.

176
00:13:36,683 --> 00:13:38,142
Now, that's holiday.

177
00:13:38,351 --> 00:13:41,771
Sweetlittle Cindy didn't know what to do.

178
00:13:41,896 --> 00:13:44,816
In her head, bum-tumbled a conflict or two.

179
00:13:45,191 --> 00:13:48,528
''If the Grinch was so bad,
then why did he save me?

180
00:13:48,653 --> 00:13:50,238
''Maybe he wasn’t so bad.''

181
00:13:51,239 --> 00:13:53,116
Maybe. Just maybe.

182
00:13:57,996 --> 00:14:00,832
No lights on in the house.
Your mom must be shopping.

183
00:14:00,915 --> 00:14:03,126
Good, l'm so glad you're home.

184
00:14:03,209 --> 00:14:06,212
l can feel it, Lou. This is the year.

185
00:14:07,088 --> 00:14:11,885
When everybody asks who has the most
spectacular lights in greater Whoville...

186
00:14:12,594 --> 00:14:15,930
...they're gonna cry out,
''Mrs. Betty Lou Who!''

187
00:14:16,598 --> 00:14:18,892
lsn't this the chandelier
from the dining room?

188
00:14:19,434 --> 00:14:21,227
lt's all for the cause, dear.

189
00:14:21,603 --> 00:14:24,856
And Cindy?
Could you be Mommy's little helper...

190
00:14:24,939 --> 00:14:27,483
...and unscrew the bulb there
from the refrigerator?

191
00:14:27,984 --> 00:14:30,111
-'Cause somehow l missed that one.
-Go on!

192
00:14:34,866 --> 00:14:40,079
Every year Martha May Whovier
has the best lights.

193
00:14:41,331 --> 00:14:42,707
Not this year.

194
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:44,375
This year...

195
00:14:44,459 --> 00:14:48,046
...l'm gonna beat
that prim, perfect little prissy--

196
00:14:48,171 --> 00:14:49,339
Betty!

197
00:14:50,340 --> 00:14:53,301
-Hi!
-Martha!

198
00:14:53,801 --> 00:14:57,555
My, l've never seen so many
beautiful Christmas lights, Betty Lou!

199
00:14:57,931 --> 00:15:01,351
l'd blow every fuse
if l tried to keep up with you, Martha May!

200
00:15:02,060 --> 00:15:04,187
lsn't this antique darling?

201
00:15:04,687 --> 00:15:08,274
lt's handcrafted and almost 100 years old.

202
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:10,860
Jeez. l'm really impressed!

203
00:15:12,070 --> 00:15:14,030
This, however, is new.

204
00:15:26,668 --> 00:15:28,711
Betty! Sweetie!

205
00:15:44,519 --> 00:15:46,312
Good night, Betty.

206
00:15:50,942 --> 00:15:53,486
-l got it!
-Honey, l've got it.

207
00:15:53,570 --> 00:15:54,654
Hello?

208
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:58,825
ls my sub-zero chillibrator running?

209
00:15:59,409 --> 00:16:02,328
-l suppose.
-You better go catch it!

210
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:13,131
That's a good one! That is rich.

211
00:16:17,176 --> 00:16:18,636
Let's go home.

212
00:16:22,974 --> 00:16:25,810
Fleas before beauty. Thank you.

213
00:16:30,148 --> 00:16:32,275
Come on, hurry up, Slowpoke.

214
00:16:46,623 --> 00:16:49,542
There's got to be a better way!

215
00:17:11,522 --> 00:17:14,067
A car would have paid for itself by now!

216
00:17:15,902 --> 00:17:18,112
Goody. Another load coming down.

217
00:17:22,951 --> 00:17:24,744
What's that stench?

218
00:17:25,453 --> 00:17:26,996
lt's fantastic!

219
00:17:29,541 --> 00:17:31,167
Max! Grab a bag.

220
00:17:32,210 --> 00:17:34,087
We'll come back for the rest.

221
00:17:34,295 --> 00:17:37,215
Of course, when l say ''we,'' l mean ''you.''

222
00:17:38,174 --> 00:17:41,177
lt's amazing
what these Whos just throw away.

223
00:17:41,344 --> 00:17:42,345
Oh, well.

224
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:47,517
One man's toxic sludge
is another man's potpourri.

225
00:17:48,142 --> 00:17:50,186
l don't know. lt's some kind of soap.

226
00:18:02,657 --> 00:18:06,327
''Where are you, Christmas?

227
00:18:06,828 --> 00:18:10,331
''Why can't l find you?

228
00:18:10,915 --> 00:18:15,879
''Why have you gone away?

229
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:22,760
''My world is changing

230
00:18:22,886 --> 00:18:26,723
''l'm rearranging

231
00:18:26,890 --> 00:18:29,642
''Does that mean Christmas

232
00:18:30,393 --> 00:18:33,730
''changes too?

233
00:18:42,739 --> 00:18:46,409
''Where are you, Christmas?

234
00:18:46,826 --> 00:18:49,787
''Do you remember

235
00:18:50,496 --> 00:18:55,919
''The girl you used to know?

236
00:18:57,295 --> 00:19:02,258
''You and l were so carefree

237
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:05,762
''Now nothing's easy

238
00:19:06,429 --> 00:19:09,515
''Did Christmas change

239
00:19:10,099 --> 00:19:15,146
''Or just

240
00:19:16,105 --> 00:19:20,401
''me?''

241
00:19:47,762 --> 00:19:48,930
Sweet!

242
00:19:58,982 --> 00:20:01,276
''Be it ever so

243
00:20:01,651 --> 00:20:02,735
''Heinous

244
00:20:02,860 --> 00:20:06,864
''There's no place like home''

245
00:20:11,744 --> 00:20:14,122
First floor, factory rejects.

246
00:20:15,498 --> 00:20:17,792
Those Whos are hard to frazzle, Max!

247
00:20:17,917 --> 00:20:21,170
But we did our worst.
And that's all that matters.

248
00:20:21,296 --> 00:20:25,049
At least l scared the bejeebles
out of that little girl at the post office.

249
00:20:25,133 --> 00:20:27,594
She'll be scarred for life, if we're lucky.

250
00:20:44,193 --> 00:20:46,237
Funny she didn't rat on us, though.

251
00:20:46,446 --> 00:20:48,573
Must be afraid of reprisals.

252
00:21:00,627 --> 00:21:01,794
Yes!

253
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:04,380
Down a size and a half!

254
00:21:05,882 --> 00:21:08,509
And this time, l'll keep it off.

255
00:21:11,012 --> 00:21:13,306
Get the stick, Max. Get the stick!

256
00:21:17,435 --> 00:21:19,062
There's no stick!

257
00:21:19,187 --> 00:21:20,647
l'm smarter.

258
00:21:27,737 --> 00:21:29,113
Any calls?

259
00:21:30,907 --> 00:21:32,700
You have no messages.

260
00:21:33,493 --> 00:21:36,663
Odd. Better check the outgoing.

261
00:21:38,206 --> 00:21:40,416
If you utter so much as one syllable...

262
00:21:40,542 --> 00:21:44,379
