264
00:21:50,009 --> 00:21:51,344
Oh, well.

265
00:21:56,766 --> 00:21:58,560
That's more like it.

266
00:22:19,163 --> 00:22:20,540
Excellent year.

267
00:22:21,583 --> 00:22:23,209
l'll tell you, Max...

268
00:22:23,418 --> 00:22:25,795
...l don't know why l ever leave this place.

269
00:22:26,170 --> 00:22:29,757
l've got all the company l need right here.

270
00:22:31,217 --> 00:22:32,802
Hello!

271
00:22:32,886 --> 00:22:34,387
Hello!

272
00:22:35,305 --> 00:22:36,556
How are you?

273
00:22:36,681 --> 00:22:37,932
How are you?

274
00:22:38,391 --> 00:22:39,976
l asked you first.

275
00:22:40,059 --> 00:22:41,311
I asked you first.

276
00:22:41,728 --> 00:22:45,815
That's really mature,
saying exactly what l say!

277
00:22:46,190 --> 00:22:49,527
Mature...exactly...what I say....

278
00:22:51,154 --> 00:22:52,155
l'm an idiot!

279
00:22:52,739 --> 00:22:54,616
You're an idiot!

280
00:22:57,869 --> 00:22:59,037
All right, fine.

281
00:22:59,162 --> 00:23:02,665
l'm not talking to you anymore.
ln fact, l'm going to whisper.

282
00:23:02,749 --> 00:23:07,128
So that by the time my voice reverberates
off the walls and gets back to me...

283
00:23:07,337 --> 00:23:10,173
...l won't be able to hear it!

284
00:23:11,466 --> 00:23:13,593
You're an idiot!

285
00:23:25,438 --> 00:23:27,815
Am l just eating because l'm bored?

286
00:23:37,992 --> 00:23:39,452
Who could that be?

287
00:23:41,579 --> 00:23:44,499
Hello, little girl.
Are you here to read to us?

288
00:23:44,707 --> 00:23:45,708
No.

289
00:23:46,209 --> 00:23:49,212
l hear you know some things
about the Grinch.

290
00:23:49,337 --> 00:23:53,091
Cindy Lou had some questions
in her curious heart.

291
00:23:53,508 --> 00:23:57,262
Why did the Grinch hate Christmas?
Where did it all start?

292
00:23:57,595 --> 00:24:00,348
With her dad's blabbacorder
she wouldn't give an inch.

293
00:24:00,473 --> 00:24:05,019
ln your own words, please tell me
everything you know about the Grinch.

294
00:24:05,478 --> 00:24:06,980
Where did he come from?

295
00:24:09,065 --> 00:24:11,359
He came the way all Who babies come.

296
00:24:12,777 --> 00:24:14,821
On calm nights...

297
00:24:14,946 --> 00:24:18,866
...baby Who girls
and tiny Who fellas...

298
00:24:19,284 --> 00:24:24,080
...drift from the sky
in their own pumbersellas.

299
00:24:31,754 --> 00:24:34,924
Hey, honey, our baby is here!

300
00:24:37,093 --> 00:24:38,970
He looks just like your boss.

301
00:24:41,264 --> 00:24:43,141
So that's how it works.

302
00:24:44,392 --> 00:24:48,771
lt was Christmas Eve,
and a strange wind blew that night.

303
00:25:15,715 --> 00:25:18,343
We were having
our annual holiday get-together.

304
00:25:41,157 --> 00:25:45,870
It was morning before anybody realized
that he was out there!

305
00:25:45,954 --> 00:25:47,038
The poor dear!

306
00:25:47,705 --> 00:25:49,082
But, you know what?

307
00:25:49,165 --> 00:25:51,209
We knew right away that he was special.

308
00:25:57,173 --> 00:25:59,300
Do you want a Christmas cookie?

309
00:25:59,425 --> 00:26:02,262
Yes, which Christmas cookie
would you like?

310
00:26:02,387 --> 00:26:03,388
Santa.

311
00:26:04,973 --> 00:26:06,349
His first words!

312
00:26:06,432 --> 00:26:08,726
Yes, that is a Santa plate.

313
00:26:08,935 --> 00:26:11,479
Do you want to hold this Santa plate?

314
00:26:19,112 --> 00:26:20,655
Santa, bye-bye!

315
00:26:25,493 --> 00:26:27,537
He was a wonderful...

316
