...maybe if you hear the truth,
you'll understand why--

333
00:27:26,137 --> 00:27:27,931
Put your back into it!

334
00:27:28,765 --> 00:27:31,601
l tried to take him under my wing.

335
00:27:32,268 --> 00:27:36,272
You don't have a chance with her.
You're 8 years old and you have a beard!

336
00:27:39,901 --> 00:27:42,445
He had hair. Not pleasant.

337
00:27:44,447 --> 00:27:45,698
He shed.

338
00:27:46,032 --> 00:27:47,033
Not right.

339
00:27:49,577 --> 00:27:52,914
You know, Christmas
is my favorite time of year.

340
00:27:53,456 --> 00:27:55,250
l just love the colors.

341
00:27:55,833 --> 00:27:57,168
The red...

342
00:27:57,502 --> 00:27:59,212
...and the green.

343
00:28:02,799 --> 00:28:04,926
Did I have a crush on the Grinch?

344
00:28:06,219 --> 00:28:07,220
Of course not.

345
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,138
l didn't ask you that.

346
00:28:11,724 --> 00:28:12,809
Right.

347
00:28:14,185 --> 00:28:16,563
For some reason,
when he came home that day...

348
00:28:16,688 --> 00:28:19,857
...he really got into the Christmas spirit
for the first time.

349
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:21,901
Perfect!

350
00:28:25,446 --> 00:28:26,531
Whoopsie!

351
00:28:33,329 --> 00:28:35,540
What a lovely family heirloom!

352
00:28:47,719 --> 00:28:49,512
The fires of love!

353
00:28:52,223 --> 00:28:54,601
This will be perfect on the top of her tree.

354
00:28:54,726 --> 00:28:57,604
Oh, Martha! Oh, Christmas!

355
00:29:03,943 --> 00:29:07,280
I want you all to look your best tomorrow.

356
00:29:08,281 --> 00:29:10,158
You don't have a chance with her.

357
00:29:10,283 --> 00:29:13,077
You're 8 years old and you have a beard!

358
00:29:28,801 --> 00:29:30,511
Has everyone given their gifts?

359
00:29:31,638 --> 00:29:33,431
-l haven't.
-What?

360
00:29:40,772 --> 00:29:42,732
Merry Christmas, Martha May.

361
00:29:44,192 --> 00:29:46,486
Why do you have a bag on your head?

362
00:29:47,237 --> 00:29:51,074
Probably because
he's embarrassed by that hideodorous gift.

363
00:29:52,867 --> 00:29:54,202
Mr. Grinch...

364
00:29:54,536 --> 00:29:56,913
...please take the bag off.

365
00:29:58,373 --> 00:29:59,457
Yes, you.

366
00:29:59,582 --> 00:30:00,750
Take it off.

367
00:30:05,797 --> 00:30:07,590
Put the book down.

368
00:30:12,095 --> 00:30:13,638
And your foot.

369
00:30:16,641 --> 00:30:18,268
Look at that hack job!

370
00:30:29,779 --> 00:30:31,739
Stupid present!

371
00:30:32,574 --> 00:30:33,950
Stupid tree!

372
00:30:34,325 --> 00:30:37,203
l hate Christmas!

373
00:30:37,453 --> 00:30:39,581
-The anger.
-The fury!

374
00:30:40,248 --> 00:30:41,791
The muscles!

375
00:30:53,511 --> 00:30:58,057
lt was a horrible day
when they were so cruel to him.

376
00:30:58,641 --> 00:30:59,809
And...

377
00:31:01,436 --> 00:31:03,062
...l could hardly bear it.

378
00:31:19,412 --> 00:31:22,248
l hate Christmas! l hate it!

379
00:31:23,416 --> 00:31:26,211
And that was the last time
we ever saw him.

380
00:31:28,713 --> 00:31:31,174
The very last time.

381
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:26,187
So, whatever the reason,
his heart or his shoes...

382
00:32:26,604 --> 00:32:28,731
...he stood outside his cave...

383
00:32:29,148 --> 00:32:31,192
...hating the Whos.

384
00:32:31,818 --> 00:32:33,528
Alphabetically.

385
00:32:35,697 --> 00:32:38,074
Aardvarkian Abakenezer Who...

386
00:32:38,366 --> 00:32:39,450
...l...

387
00:32:39,826 --> 00:32:43,162
...hate you!

388
