''Whobilation, Whobilation''

402
00:33:38,384 --> 00:33:39,552
-Dad?
-Yeah.

403
00:33:39,636 --> 00:33:43,723
l've been thinking about the Whobilation
and l may do something drastic.

404
00:33:43,806 --> 00:33:45,934
That's fine, dear. Ask your mother.

405
00:33:46,017 --> 00:33:48,561
-Where did she go?
-Honey!

406
00:33:48,645 --> 00:33:50,271
Honey! Hi!

407
00:33:51,356 --> 00:33:55,193
Look, l just found the cutest light
for my Christmas display.

408
00:33:56,569 --> 00:33:58,780
Hurry up, we're gonna be late. Come on.

409
00:34:17,799 --> 00:34:20,009
And now, the nominations...

410
00:34:20,093 --> 00:34:22,845
...for that Who among us
who best typifies...

411
00:34:22,929 --> 00:34:26,432
...the qualities of Whodom and Whodery...

412
00:34:26,558 --> 00:34:30,812
...the Whoville holiday cheermeister!

413
00:34:39,153 --> 00:34:42,031
Do l hear a nomination?

414
00:34:42,115 --> 00:34:43,449
l nominate the Grinch!

415
00:34:45,535 --> 00:34:48,413
-The Grinch?
-The Grinch?

416
00:34:50,582 --> 00:34:52,542
My, my, my.

417
00:34:52,625 --> 00:34:55,962
What an altruistic daughter
you have there, Lou!

418
00:34:57,088 --> 00:34:58,673
Thank you.

419
00:35:00,174 --> 00:35:01,426
Cindy?

420
00:35:04,137 --> 00:35:06,514
Let me quote a verse...

421
00:35:07,223 --> 00:35:09,100
...from The Book of Who.

422
00:35:09,767 --> 00:35:10,935
Thank you.

423
00:35:11,019 --> 00:35:16,399
''The term 'Grinchy' shall apply
when Christmas spirit is in short supply.''

424
00:35:16,482 --> 00:35:19,819
Now, l ask you: Does that sound
like our holiday cheermeister?

425
00:35:20,236 --> 00:35:24,699
True, Mr. May-Who.
But The Book of Who says this too:

426
00:35:24,782 --> 00:35:27,327
''No matter how different
a Who may appear...

427
00:35:27,410 --> 00:35:30,330
''...he will always be welcomed
with holiday cheer.''

428
00:35:33,791 --> 00:35:36,628
Yes, the book also says, the....

429
00:35:36,711 --> 00:35:38,087
''The award...

430
00:35:38,171 --> 00:35:41,007
''...cannot go to the Grinch, because...

431
00:35:41,090 --> 00:35:44,928
''...sometimes things
get the lead-pipe cinch.''

432
00:35:45,136 --> 00:35:47,430
You made that up! lt doesn't say that.

433
00:35:48,014 --> 00:35:49,724
No, it does.

434
00:35:51,059 --> 00:35:52,060
What page?

435
00:35:55,396 --> 00:35:58,399
Lost my place, but it's....

436
00:35:58,942 --> 00:36:00,109
lt's in here!

437
00:36:00,193 --> 00:36:02,153
But the book does say:

438
00:36:02,237 --> 00:36:05,990
''The cheermeister is the one
who deserves a back slap or a toast.

439
00:36:06,324 --> 00:36:09,577
''And it goes to the soul at Christmas
who needs it most.''

440
00:36:09,661 --> 00:36:12,288
And l believe that soul is the Grinch.

441
00:36:13,373 --> 00:36:17,752
And if you're the Whos l hope you are,
you will too.

442
00:36:18,878 --> 00:36:20,463
She's right!

443
00:36:25,718 --> 00:36:26,803
Fine.

444
00:36:27,178 --> 00:36:30,598
You people want to waste
a perfectly good nomination...

445
00:36:30,723 --> 00:36:32,433
...why, it's up to you.

446
00:36:32,559 --> 00:36:35,270
But l am telling you...

447
00:36:35,353 --> 00:36:38,690
...the Grinch will never come down.

448
00:36:38,815 --> 00:36:41,734
And when he doesn't,
the Mayor will wear the crown.

449
00:36:41,859 --> 00:36:43,903
Well, more or less.

450
00:36:44,862 --> 00:36:47,657
''Deck your heart with jollity

