''Mr. Grinch

786
01:02:57,602 --> 01:02:59,395
''You're a bad banana

787
01:02:59,854 --> 01:03:03,274
''With a greasy black peel

788
01:03:09,030 --> 01:03:12,033
''Just face the music, you're a monster

789
01:03:12,700 --> 01:03:14,911
''Mr. Grinch, yes, you are

790
01:03:15,411 --> 01:03:19,499
''Your heart's an empty hole

791
01:03:19,874 --> 01:03:23,628
''Your brain is full of spiders
You got garlic in your soul

792
01:03:23,753 --> 01:03:26,130
''Mr. Grinch

793
01:03:27,298 --> 01:03:29,592
''I wouldn't touch you with a

794
01:03:30,677 --> 01:03:34,180
''thirty-nine-and-a-half foot pole''

795
01:03:45,900 --> 01:03:49,070
l asked for three-quarters, not five-eighths.

796
01:03:49,279 --> 01:03:50,738
Stay focused!

797
01:03:57,036 --> 01:04:00,373
''You know, if you asked
the who's who of Whoville

798
01:04:01,833 --> 01:04:05,336
''No one would deny it''

799
01:04:25,231 --> 01:04:27,692
Air bag is a little slow.

800
01:04:30,111 --> 01:04:32,655
But that's what these tests are for!

801
01:04:33,573 --> 01:04:35,450
''You're a vile one

802
01:04:36,034 --> 01:04:37,452
''Mr. Grinch

803
01:04:38,578 --> 01:04:42,498
''You have termites in your smile

804
01:04:43,124 --> 01:04:47,587
''You have all the tender sweetness
Of a seasick crocodile

805
01:04:47,670 --> 01:04:49,881
''Mr. Grinch

806
01:04:51,174 --> 01:04:53,468
''Given the choice between you

807
01:04:53,551 --> 01:04:56,888
''l'd take the seasick crocodile''

808
01:05:19,786 --> 01:05:23,373
Fat boy should be finishing up
anytime now.

809
01:05:24,374 --> 01:05:26,251
Talk about a recluse.

810
01:05:26,334 --> 01:05:30,713
He only comes out once a year,
and he never catches any flak for it!

811
01:05:32,048 --> 01:05:34,801
Probably lives up there to avoid the taxes.

812
01:05:36,844 --> 01:05:39,389
Merry Christmas!

813
01:05:41,224 --> 01:05:42,475
Oopsie.

814
01:05:43,810 --> 01:05:45,937
Forgot about the reindeer.

815
01:05:46,771 --> 01:05:49,440
Did that stop the old Grinch?

816
01:05:50,108 --> 01:05:51,734
No.

817
01:05:51,859 --> 01:05:53,903
The Grinch simply said:

818
01:05:54,320 --> 01:05:56,864
lf l can't find a reindeer...

819
01:05:57,699 --> 01:06:00,952
...l'll make one instead.

820
01:06:05,331 --> 01:06:09,002
Oh, Max!

821
01:06:12,297 --> 01:06:14,257
So he called his dog Max...

822
01:06:15,008 --> 01:06:16,885
...and he took some red thread...

823
01:06:17,093 --> 01:06:20,513
...and tied a big horn on top of his head.

824
01:06:24,183 --> 01:06:25,184
All right.

825
01:06:25,727 --> 01:06:28,605
You're a reindeer. Here's your motivation.

826
01:06:28,897 --> 01:06:31,858
You're Rudolph, a freak with a red nose,
nobody likes you.

827
01:06:31,941 --> 01:06:34,903
Then one day,
Santa picks you and you save Christmas.

828
01:06:37,322 --> 01:06:39,699
No, forget that part. We'll improvise.

829
01:06:39,824 --> 01:06:42,285
Just keep it kind of loosey-goosey.

830
01:06:42,452 --> 01:06:44,579
You hate Christmas! You're gonna steal it!

831
01:06:44,996 --> 01:06:48,499
Saving Christmas was a lousy ending.
Way too commercial.

832
01:06:50,043 --> 01:06:51,502
Action!

833
01:06:54,172 --> 01:06:55,340
Brilliant!

834
01:06:55,757 --> 01:06:57,717
You reject your own nose...

835
01:06:57,842 --> 01:07:00,511
...because it represents the
glitter of commercialism!

836
01:07:00,595 --> 01:07:02,388
Why didn't l think of that?

837
01:07:02,472 --> 01:07:04,682
Cut, print, check the gate. Moving on.

838
01:07:14,651 --> 01:07:15,985
That...

839
01:07:16,110 --> 01:07:17,528
...feels...

840
01:07:17,612 --> 01:07:19,739
...good.

841
01:07:31,084 --> 01:07:33,878
Here goes nothin', hot dog!

842
01:07:39,717 --> 01:07:40,802
Wow!

843
01:07:54,941 --> 01:07:57,318
This is nuts!

844
01:07:59,362 --> 01:08:01,406
On, Crasher! On, Thrasher!

845
01:08:01,739 --> 01:08:03,866
On, Vomit and Blitzkrieg!

846
01:08:12,709 --> 01:08:14,168
We're gonna die!

847
01:08:14,294 --> 01:08:16,004
We're gonna die!

848
01:08:16,379 --> 01:08:19,799
l'm going to throw up,
and then l'm gonna die!

849
01:08:22,218 --> 01:08:25,305
Mommy, tell it to stop!

850
01:08:44,282 --> 01:08:47,035
Almost lost my cool there.

851
01:08:52,248 --> 01:08:56,461
All their windows were dark.
Quiet snow filled the air.

852
01:08:56,669 --> 01:09:00,924
All the Whos were all dreaming
sweet dreams without care...

853
01:09:01,049 --> 01:09:03,718
...when he came to the first
little house on the square.

854
01:09:03,801 --> 01:09:05,845
Welcome to Whoville, Max.

855
01:09:13,770 --> 01:09:14,854
Betty?

856
01:09:15,146 --> 01:09:16,397
-Betty?
-What?

857
01:09:16,481 --> 01:09:18,441
Did you hear something?

858
01:09:20,401 --> 01:09:21,736
lt's Santa!

859
01:09:21,819 --> 01:09:23,780
Go right back to sleep.

860
01:09:29,160 --> 01:09:32,497
Come on, Max. lt's our first stop.

861
01:09:32,747 --> 01:09:34,958
The old Grinchy Claus hissed.

862
01:09:35,083 --> 01:09:37,919
And he climbed to the roof,
empty bags in his fist.

863
01:09:38,002 --> 01:09:41,339
He'd slide down the chimney.
A rather tight pinch.

864
01:09:41,631 --> 01:09:44,717
But if Santa could do it,
then so could the Grinch.

865
01:09:45,176 --> 01:09:48,763
He's planning a double-twisting
interrupted forward-flying 2-and-a-half...

866
01:09:48,846 --> 01:09:50,473
...with a combo tuck and pike.

867
01:09:50,598 --> 01:09:52,225
High degree of difficulty.

868
01:10:00,275 --> 01:10:03,611
He got stuck only once,
for a moment or two.

869
01:10:03,736 --> 01:10:07,407
Blasted water weight!
Goes right to my hips.

870
01:10:17,375 --> 01:10:20,253
Then he stuck his head
out of the fireplace flue.

871
01:10:21,629 --> 01:10:23,923
A little more stealth, please.

872
01:10:24,299 --> 01:10:26,759
Where the little Who stockings
all hung in a row.

873
01:10:26,843 --> 01:10:27,927
These stockings...

874
01:10:28,052 --> 01:10:28,970
...he grinned...

875
01:10:29,095 --> 01:10:30,889
...are the first thing to go.

876
01:10:31,347 --> 01:10:33,808
Okay, fellas. Show time.

877
01:11:05,590 --> 01:11:07,717
Then he slunk to the icebox.

878
01:11:09,052 --> 01:11:10,136
Slunk?

879
01:11:12,347 --> 01:11:16,267
He eyed the Whos' feast.
He took the Who pudding.

880
01:11:17,435 --> 01:11:19,562
He took the roast beast.

881
01:11:20,104 --> 01:11:21,189
Hike!

882
01:11:22,523 --> 01:11:24,817
He cleaned out that icebox
as quick as a flash.

883
01:11:24,943 --> 01:11:28,863
Why, that Grinch,
he even took their last can of Who hash.

884
01:11:29,948 --> 01:11:33,451
Then he stuffed all the food
up the chimney with glee.

885
01:11:34,118 --> 01:11:35,745
And now...

886
01:11:35,870 --> 01:11:37,747
...grinned the Grinch...

887
01:11:39,707 --> 01:11:41,501
...l'll stuff up the tree.

888
01:11:41,584 --> 01:11:44,587
And the Grinch grabbed the tree,
and he started to shove...

889
01:11:45,296 --> 01:11:48,967
...when he heard a small sound
like the coo of a dove.

890
01:11:49,092 --> 01:11:50,510
Excuse me.

891
01:11:56,516 --> 01:11:59,769
The Grinch had been caught
by this tiny Who daughter...

892
01:11:59,978 --> 01:12:02,522
...who'd got out of bed
for a cup of cold water.

893
01:12:02,647 --> 01:12:06,067
Santa Claus?
What are you doing with our tree?

894
01:12:06,609 --> 01:12:10,530
But, you know, that old Grinch
was so smart and so slick...

895
01:12:12,156 --> 01:12:15,076
...he thought up a lie,
and he thought it up quick.

896
01:12:15,618 --> 01:12:16,870
Why...

897
01:12:16,995 --> 01:12:19,831
...my sweet little tot.

898
01:12:20,081 --> 01:12:21,708
The fake Santa Claus lied.

899
01:12:22,083 --> 01:12:24,377
There's a light on this tree...

900
01:12:25,086 --> 01:12:26,504
...that won't...

901
01:12:26,588 --> 01:12:28,548
...light on one side.

902
01:12:29,007 --> 01:12:33,094
So l'm taking it home
to my workshop, my dear.

903
01:12:38,182 --> 01:12:40,310
l'll fix it up there...

904
01:12:40,727 --> 01:12:44,397
...and l'll bring it back here.

905
01:12:46,232 --> 01:12:48,192
Santa, what's Christmas really about?

906
01:12:48,484 --> 01:12:50,278
Vengeance!

907
01:12:52,030 --> 01:12:53,281
l mean...

908
01:12:55,909 --> 01:12:57,410
...presents...

909
01:12:58,494 --> 01:12:59,954
...l suppose.

910
01:13:04,000 --> 01:13:05,793
l was afraid of that.

911
01:13:07,295 --> 01:13:10,465
And his fib fooled the child.

912
01:13:10,757 --> 01:13:14,093
Then he patted her head,
and he got her a drink...

913
01:13:14,219 --> 01:13:16,596
...and he sent her to bed.

914
01:13:24,354 --> 01:13:25,355
Santa?

915
01:13:26,064 --> 01:13:29,400
-What?
-Don't forget the Grinch.

916
01:13:30,193 --> 01:13:32,153
l know he's mean and hairy and smelly.

917
01:13:34,113 --> 01:13:36,574
His hands might be cold and clammy.

918
01:13:38,076 --> 01:13:41,579
But l think he's actually kind of sweet.

919
01:13:41,955 --> 01:13:43,039
Sweet?

920
01:13:50,755 --> 01:13:52,549
You think he's sweet?

921
01:13:53,424 --> 01:13:55,218
Merry Christmas, Santa.

922
01:14:02,308 --> 01:14:05,228
And when Cindy Lou
went up with her cup...

923
01:14:05,353 --> 01:14:06,980
Nice kid.

924
01:14:07,897 --> 01:14:10,525
Bad judge of character.

925
01:14:11,609 --> 01:14:14,404
...he went to the chimney
and stuffed the tree up.

926
01:14:22,495 --> 01:14:25,832
And the last thing he took
was the log for their fire.

927
01:14:25,915 --> 01:14:30,086
On their walls he left nothing
but some hooks and some wire.

928
01:14:30,211 --> 01:14:32,964
And the one speck of food
that he'd left in the house...

929
01:14:33,047 --> 01:14:36,384
...was a crumb that was even
too small for a mouse.

930
01:14:39,512 --> 01:14:43,766
Then he slithered and slunk,
with a smile most unpleasant...

931
01:14:43,933 --> 01:14:47,687
...around each Who home,
and he took every present.

932
01:14:58,948 --> 01:15:00,033
Clearance sale.

933
01:15:00,158 --> 01:15:02,118
Everything must go.

934
01:15:15,173 --> 01:15:17,133
What now?

935
01:15:52,710 --> 01:15:53,711
Martha...

936
01:15:53,962 --> 01:15:57,799
...have you ever kissed a man
who lost his tonsils twice?

937
01:15:59,050 --> 01:16:00,843
No, silly!

938
01:16:04,931 --> 01:16:08,518
But it's an experience
that l've always longed for.

939
01:16:08,935 --> 01:16:10,645
Kiss me, you fool!

940
01:17:33,436 --> 01:17:35,480
What are you laughing at...

941
01:17:36,314 --> 01:17:38,274
...Rudolph?

942
01:17:39,400 --> 01:17:41,444
lt's all you, Maxie!

943
01:17:41,527 --> 01:17:44,948
3,000 feet up,
up the side of Mount Crumpit...

944
01:17:45,031 --> 01:17:48,618
...he rode with his load
to the tiptop to dump it.

945
01:17:58,545 --> 01:18:01,714
We did it!

946
01:18:06,970 --> 01:18:08,930
We did it! We did it!

947
01:18:09,556 --> 01:18:11,599
That wasn't so bad, was it, Max?

948
01:18:15,478 --> 01:18:17,272
They'll be waking up now.

949
01:18:19,482 --> 01:18:23,236
And l know just what they'll do.

950
01:18:24,070 --> 01:18:26,197
All those Whos...

951
01:18:26,614 --> 01:18:28,324
...down in Whoville...

952
01:18:28,449 --> 01:18:30,743
...will all cry.

953
01:18:48,887 --> 01:18:51,514
What an embarrassment!
l've been robbed!

954
01:19:21,586 --> 01:19:23,796
Mayor May-Who? Oh, dear.

955
01:19:31,679 --> 01:19:34,224
l wonder who could have done this.

956
01:19:36,184 --> 01:19:37,685
Tell you people one thing:

957
01:19:38,311 --> 01:19:39,854
lnvite the Grinch...

958
01:19:40,480 --> 01:19:42,357
...destroy Christmas.

959
01:19:42,690 --> 01:19:44,567
lnvite the Grinch...

960
01:19:44,692 --> 01:19:47,487
...destroy Christmas!

961
01:19:50,657 --> 01:19:53,409
But did anyone listen to me?

962
01:19:53,493 --> 01:19:55,203
-l did.
-No.

963
01:19:55,286 --> 01:19:58,289
You choose to listen...

964
01:19:58,456 --> 01:20:03,086
...to a little not-to-be-taken-seriously girl...

965
01:20:04,045 --> 01:20:07,298
...who hasn't even grown into her nose yet.

966
01:20:08,883 --> 01:20:11,970
Cindy, l hope you're very proud...

967
01:20:12,387 --> 01:20:13,638
...of what you've done.

968
01:20:22,730 --> 01:20:24,440
lf she isn't, l am.

969
01:20:26,609 --> 01:20:28,486
l'm glad he took our presents.

970
01:20:30,405 --> 01:20:32,198
-What?
-l....

971
01:20:34,993 --> 01:20:37,120
-l'm glad.
-He's glad.

972
01:20:37,996 --> 01:20:40,957
You're glad.
You're glad everything is gone.

973
01:20:42,250 --> 01:20:46,337
You're glad that the Grinch
virtually wrecked....

974
01:20:46,421 --> 01:20:48,882
No, not wrecked, pulverized Christmas.

975
01:20:48,965 --> 01:20:50,675
ls that what l'm hearing?

976
01:20:51,759 --> 01:20:53,970
You can't hurt Christmas, Mr. Mayor...

977
01:20:54,053 --> 01:20:58,057
...because it isn't about the gifts
or the contests or the fancy lights.

978
01:20:58,141 --> 01:21:01,394
That's what Cindy's been trying
to tell everyone.

979
01:21:01,936 --> 01:21:04,147
And me. She's been trying to tell me.

980
01:21:04,230 --> 01:21:07,650
What is wrong with you? This is a child.

981
01:21:08,526 --> 01:21:10,153
She's my child.

982
01:21:10,236 --> 01:21:13,072
And she happens to be right, by the way.

983
01:21:21,664 --> 01:21:25,877
l don't need anything more for Christmas
than this right here, my family.

984
01:21:29,130 --> 01:21:32,467
-Merry Christmas, everybody!
-Merry Christmas!

985
01:21:33,968 --> 01:21:37,972
Merry Christmas, you hunk of burnin' Who!

986
01:21:45,396 --> 01:21:47,023
Give me a break.

987
01:21:54,864 --> 01:21:55,949
Merry Christmas!

988
01:22:08,586 --> 01:22:09,754
Mr. Grinch?

989
01:22:11,214 --> 01:22:13,174
Mr. Grinch?

990
01:22:13,258 --> 01:22:16,094
Now for the final note in my symphony...

991
01:22:16,177 --> 01:22:19,180
...of downright nasty not-niceness!

992
01:22:19,514 --> 01:22:22,767
The crescendo of my odious opus!

993
01:22:28,856 --> 01:22:31,401
The wailing and the gnashing of teeth.

994
01:22:31,901 --> 01:22:36,364
The bellowing of the bitterly bummed out!

995
01:22:36,906 --> 01:22:40,076
lt'll be like music to my ears!

996
01:22:48,418 --> 01:22:52,630
Then the Grinch heard
a sound rising over the snow.

997
01:22:52,755 --> 01:22:56,801
It started in low. Then it started to grow.

998
01:22:59,178 --> 01:23:01,639
But the sound wasn’t sad.

999
01:23:02,307 --> 01:23:05,101
Why, this sounded merry.

1000
01:23:05,977 --> 01:23:08,354
But it was merry.

1001
01:23:08,521 --> 01:23:09,689
Very.

1002
01:23:09,898 --> 01:23:13,818
Every Who down in Whoville,
the tall and the small...

1003
01:23:13,943 --> 01:23:17,196
...were singing without any presents at all.

1004
01:23:23,203 --> 01:23:25,830
He hadn’t stopped Christmas from coming.

1005
01:23:26,122 --> 01:23:27,123
It came.

1006
01:23:27,248 --> 01:23:30,501
Somehow or other, it came just the same!

1007
01:23:34,380 --> 01:23:35,924
Mr. Grinch?

1008
01:23:38,718 --> 01:23:42,555
And the Grinch,
with his Grinch feet ice-cold in the snow...

1009
01:23:42,639 --> 01:23:45,308
...stood puzzling and puzzling.

1010
01:23:45,642 --> 01:23:47,769
How could it be so?

1011
01:23:48,061 --> 01:23:49,854
lt came without ribbons!

1012
01:23:50,271 --> 01:23:52,649
lt came without tags!

1013
01:23:52,899 --> 01:23:56,236
lt came without packages, boxes or bags!

1014
01:23:59,322 --> 01:24:02,158
And he puzzled and puzzled...

1015
01:24:02,242 --> 01:24:04,702
...till his puzzler was sore.

1016
01:24:07,121 --> 01:24:11,042
Then the Grinch thought of something...

1017
01:24:11,167 --> 01:24:12,877
...he hadn't before.

1018
01:24:13,127 --> 01:24:14,379
Maybe...

1019
01:24:15,630 --> 01:24:16,881
...Christmas...

1020
01:24:16,965 --> 01:24:18,841
...he thought...

1021
01:24:21,135 --> 01:24:24,806
...doesn't come from a store.

1022
01:24:28,560 --> 01:24:30,186
Maybe Christmas...

1023
01:24:31,521 --> 01:24:32,939
...perhaps...

1024
01:24:38,820 --> 01:24:41,281
...means a little bit more.

1025
01:25:14,647 --> 01:25:16,232
Help me!

1026
01:25:17,025 --> 01:25:18,192
l'm...

1027
01:25:19,235 --> 01:25:20,695
...feeling!

1028
01:25:27,493 --> 01:25:29,621
And what happened then...

1029
01:25:29,954 --> 01:25:32,498
...well, in Whoville they say...

1030
01:25:32,749 --> 01:25:35,418
...that the Grinch's small heart...

1031
01:25:35,501 --> 01:25:39,422
...grew three sizes that day.

1032
01:26:10,828 --> 01:26:14,082
What's happening to me?

1033
01:26:37,564 --> 01:26:38,898
l'm all...

1034
01:26:40,233 --> 01:26:42,026
...toasty inside.

1035
01:26:49,200 --> 01:26:51,578
And l'm leaking.

1036
01:26:54,914 --> 01:26:55,999
Oh, Max.

1037
01:26:59,460 --> 01:27:01,671
l love you!

1038
01:27:09,721 --> 01:27:12,807
All right, that's enough.
Knock it off. Beat it!

1039
01:27:13,474 --> 01:27:15,101
Get out of here!

1040
01:27:15,268 --> 01:27:17,145
One step at a time.

1041
01:27:25,528 --> 01:27:28,615
No. The sleigh. The presents.

1042
01:27:28,823 --> 01:27:30,199
They'll be destroyed!

1043
01:27:30,283 --> 01:27:31,659
And l care!

1044
01:27:31,910 --> 01:27:34,704
What is the deal?

1045
01:27:35,538 --> 01:27:37,040
Wait!

